[[File:Map Gallia Tribes Towns.png|thumb|Map of ancient Gaule.]]
The '''Gabali''' were a [[Gauls|Gallic]] Tribe from [[Gallia Aquitania]], in the mountainous region, where the ''Oltis'' ([[Lot (river)|Lot]]) and the ''Elaver'' ([[Allier (river)|Allier]]) emerge. They were subject, and allied to the [[Averni]]. They are mentioned in Book VII of [[Commentarii de Bello Gallico|Caesar's Commentaries]]. During [[Caesar's conquest of Gaul]] they were raiding the country of the [[Ruteni|Provincial Ruteni]], and they were among the tribes that sent relief troops to the Gallic army trying to break the siege in [[Siege of Alesia|Alesia]].<ref>http://195.220.134.232/numerisation/tires-a-part-www-nb/0000002001876.pdf</ref>

